Rubber example

Week 2

1 Libs

pacman::p_load(tidyverse, gglm)

2 Overview

We want to predict the wear and tear of rubber tyres \(gm/hr\) using hardness of the rubber (Shore units) and tensile strength \(kg/m^2\)

3 Read in data

data(Rubber, package = "MASS")

4 Clean data

rubber <- tibble(Rubber)
rubber

5 EDA

skimr::skim_without_charts(rubber)

rubber %>%

6 Model

rubber_lm <- lm(loss ~ tens + hard, data = rubber)
summary(rubber_lm)

rubber_null <- lm(loss ~ 1, data = rubber)
anova(rubber_null, rubber_lm)

7 Check model

gglm::gglm(rubber_lm)

plot(rubber_lm)

8 Prediction

new_pt <- tibble(
  hard = 70, 
  tens = 180
)
new_pt
predict(rubber_lm, newdata = new_pt)
##        1 
## 177.8269
predict(rubber_lm, newdata = new_pt, interval = "confidence")
##        fit      lwr      upr
## 1 177.8269 164.1513 191.5025
predict(rubber_lm, newdata = new_pt, interval = "prediction")
##        fit      lwr      upr
## 1 177.8269 101.7182 253.9356
new_pts <- tibble(
  tens = mean(rubber$tens), 
  hard = seq(min(rubber$hard), max(rubber$hard), length = 100)
)
new_pts
pred_int <- predict(rubber_lm, new_pts, interval = "prediction")
pred_conf <- predict(rubber_lm, new_pts, interval = "confidence")
new_pts %>% 
  add_column(
    pred = pred_int[, 'fit'],
    pred_lwr = pred_int[, 'lwr'],
    pred_upr = pred_int[, 'upr'],
    conf_lwr = pred_conf[, 'lwr'],
    conf_upr = pred_conf[, 'upr'],
  ) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-c(tens, hard)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(hard, value, col = name)) + 
  geom_line() + 
  geom_point(aes(y = loss), data = rubber, col = "black")
